The boys upstairs only have to make one solid change for us to be more effective tanks.  They need us to be able to generate more aggro.  Think about this for a minute please.  What generates more aggro on the hate list right now?<br>
<br>
EVERYTHING.....slows, stuns by casters, lifedraws etc generate MORE aggro than the BoC (hate generating proc 700) as an example.  All they have to do is reverse this and do one of two things (which they talked about in new combat skills upcoming this month).  Either make warrior weapons generate more aggro which would be a headache changing every weapon out there to do this as many of our weapons can be used by other classes also OR....put in a new combat skill ie Dec 16th patch to generate more aggro even on top of say using a BoC and putting a 600 more hate generating aggro augmentation on it and praying you can generate more aggro before the casters slow or stun or lifedraw hits the mob.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong I have 160AA and I duel wield a BoC and a SoD and no anger 3 augmentation's added to them as of yet.  I can hold aggro say 70% of the time but the following is true.  If a casters slow or stun or lifedraw or snare hits the mob forget about holding that aggro and btw thats after hitting the mob with 5 procs off the BoC and another 13 off the SoD.<br>
<br>
I did some tests with a snare weapon (Anklesmasher) and with a SoD and I had  aggro 100% of the time.  My snare (or even attempts at snare) raised a lot more aggro than with my SoD and a BoC.  Here is the kicker.  I had 2 wizards 65 in group nuking the crap out of mob along with a SK lifedrawing the crap out of the mob and I still held aggro.  I switched back to the SoD and BoC and lost the aggro again.  We tested this out several times.<br>
<br>
So...an easy fix.  Put our anger and other hate generating proc's (warrior only) and taunt button above all those casters spells and we will be fixed for generating aggro.<br>
<br>
Okay that takes care of aggro.  Now for DPS.  Hmm..an interesting subject.  Lets see with my 160AA I do about 124 DPS now on a high and 95 on a low.  Anyway as a tank we want more aggro instead.  Thats why they call us tanks.  If ya want more DPS then get AA points in Flurry, Combat Fury, Ambidexerity, Double Riposte, Ferocity, Flash of Steel, Fury of the Ages, Ingenuity, Raging Flurry, and Tactical Mastery.  You will be amazed on how much more dps you get from training in those skills.<br>
<br>
